    "en": {
      "title": "Dates to inquire into the facts of the petition against Dhammika",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Supreme Court today (01) ordered that the case be called on the 13th to verify the facts regarding the fundamental rights petitions filed by the executive committee member of the People's Struggle Movement, Mr. Duminda Nagamuwa and others, against the appointment of prominent businessman Dhammika Perera as a National List Member of Parliament.",
        "Such orders were issued today (01) when this petition was called before a Supreme Court bench consisting of Mr. Priyantha Jayawardena, Mr. Yasanta Kodagoda and Mr. Arjuna Obeysekera.",
        "Duminda Nagamuwa, member of the People's Struggle Executive Committee, Professor Ratnajeevan Hoole, and Nagananda Kodithuvakku, General Secretary of the Praideh Peramuna, have been named as respondents in this petition.",
        "These petitions have been presented before the Supreme Court stating that the appointment of businessman Mr. Dhammika Perera as a National List Member of Parliament contrary to the provisions of the constitution has violated the fundamental rights of the people themselves."
      ],
